7.4 . All claims or demands for indemnification under Sections 7.1 and 7.2 shall be asserted and resolved as follows:
Indemnification Procedures
(a) As soon as is reasonably practicable after any Parent Indemnified Party or Company Indemnified Party becomes aware of any claim, event or circumstance (a "") that has or might give rise to an indemnification obligation under Section 7.1 or Section 7.2 of this Agreement, such Parent Indemnified Party or Company Indemnified Party, as the case may be (an ""), shall give written notice thereof (a "") to the party or parties from which indemnification is sought (the ""). The Claim Notice shall describe the Claim in reasonable detail and shall indicate the amount (estimated if necessary and to the extent feasible) of the Damages that have been or may be suffered by the Indemnified Person. The failure of any Indemnified Person to promptly give the Indemnifying Persons a Claim Notice shall not preclude such Indemnified Person from obtaining indemnification under this Article VII, except to the extent, and only to the extent, that such Indemnified Person's failure has actually prejudiced the rights or increased the Damages and obligations of any of the Indemnifying Persons hereunder.
