Officer's Certificate
 
 
 
 
 
 
Based upon the foregoing, but subject to the assumptions, qualifications, and limitations set forth herein, we are of the opinion that:
1.(a) The Borrower is a corporation duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Delaware and, based solely on a certificate of the Delaware Secretary of State, is in good standing and has a legal corporate existence.
(b) State Industries is a corporation duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Tennessee and, based solely on a certificate of the Tennessee Secretary of State, (i) has paid all fees, taxes and penalties owed to the State of Tennessee (as reflected in the records of the Tennessee Secretary of State and the Tennessee Department of Revenue) which affect the existence/authorization of the business, (ii) has filed the most recent corporation annual report required, (iii) has appointed a registered agent and registered office in the State of Tennessee, (iv) has not filed Articles of Dissolution or Articles of Termination and (v) a decree of judicial dissolution has not been filed.
(c) American Water is a corporation duly organized under the laws of the State of Nevada and, based solely on a certificate of the Nevada Secretary of State, existing under and by virtue of the laws of the State of Nevada since December 17, 1996, and is in good standing in the State of Nevada.
2. Based on a review of the signature pages of the Borrower, the Loan Documents to which the Borrower is a party have been duly executed and delivered on behalf of the Borrower. Based on a review of the signature pages of the Guarantors, the Guaranty has been duly executed and delivered on behalf of each Guarantor.
3. (a) The Borrower has the corporate power to enter into, and perform its obligations under, the Loan Documents. The execution, delivery, and performance of the Loan Documents have been duly authorized by all necessary corporate action on the part of the Borrower.
(b) The Guarantors have the corporate power to enter into, and perform their respective obligations under, the Guaranty. The execution, delivery, and performance of the Guaranty have been duly authorized by all necessary corporate action on the part of each Guarantor.
 
4. The Loan Documents to which an Opinion Party is a party are the valid and binding obligations of such Opinion Party enforceable against it in accordance with their terms.
5. The execution and delivery of, and performance by the Opinion Parties of their respective obligations under, the Loan Documents do not: (a) constitute a breach or violation of the organizational documents of the Borrower or the Guarantors; (b) result in a violation of any applicable law, statute, or regulation of the United States or the State of Illinois (other than those laws, rules, and regulations specifically excluded below or otherwise specifically addressed in this opinion) which, in our experience, is normally applicable to transactions of the type contemplated by the Loan Documents, without our having made any special investigation as to the applicability of any specific law, rule or regulation; (c) result in a violation of any judgment, order, writ, injunction, decree, determination, or award of which we have knowledge; or (d) constitute an event of default under or result in a breach or violation of any material contract which affects or purports to affect the Borrower's right to borrow money or the Guarantors' rights to incur contingent obligations that is publicly filed by the Borrower with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the "") and listed in the exhibit index of the Borrower's Annual Report on Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2009, as filed with the SEC on February 26, 2010, or publicly filed or required to be publicly filed by the Borrower as a material contract with the SEC as an exhibit to any Form 10-Q or Form 8-K filed subsequent to February 26, 2010.
SEC
6. No authorization, consent, approval, or other action by, and no notice to or filing with, any governmental authority or regulatory body is required to be obtained or made by the Borrower or the Guarantors for the due execution and delivery of, or performance of their respective payment obligations under, any of the Loan Documents except (a) such as have been duly obtained or made and are in full force and effect and (b) such as may be required by orders, decrees, and the like that are specifically applicable to the Borrower or the Guarantors and of which we have no knowledge.
