Section 2.06. .
Earn-Out Payment
(a) At the end of the Earn-Out Period, if Revenue for the Earn-Out Period (the "") exceeds Two Hundred And Sixteen Million Dollars ($216,000,000), Buyer shall pay or cause to be paid to Sellers in accordance with this cash in an amount equal to the product of (i) 1.09375 times (ii) the difference of the Earn-Out Period Revenue minus Two Hundred And Sixteen Million Dollars ($216,000,000), up to a maximum total payment of Thirty-Five Million Dollars ($35,000,000) (the ""). In the event that Earn-Out Period Revenue is less than or equal to Two Hundred And Sixteen Million Dollars ($216,000,000), the Earn-Out Payment shall be zero and Buyer shall have no further obligation with respect to the Earn-Out Payment.
