Section 9.05. .
Indemnification Procedures
(a) The Party seeking indemnification under this (the "") agrees to give prompt notice to any Party against whom indemnity is sought (the "") of the assertion of any claim, or the commencement of any Legal Proceeding in respect of which indemnity may be sought pursuant to this and shall provide the Indemnifying Party such information with respect thereto that the Indemnifying Party may reasonably request. The failure to so notify the Indemnifying Party shall not relieve the Indemnifying Party of its obligations hereunder, except to the extent that such failure shall have actually prejudiced the Indemnifying Party.
